{{Quote|Impossibly huge. A schoolboy fancy?''"<br />"''Not at all. Quite doable, though expensive.|Raith Sienar, presenting his design to [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Wilhuff Tarkin]]|<ref name="RP">''[[Rogue Planet]]''</ref>}}
The '''Expeditionary Battle Planetoid''' was a theoretical spherical [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]] conceptualized by [[Raith Sienar/Legends|Raith Sienar]] in [[29 BBY/Legends|29 BBY]]. It was one of the precursors to the finalized [[Death Star/Legends|Death Stars]].<ref name="RP" />

==Description==
{{Quote|It's a dream, but an achievable dream, given certain advances in hypermatter technology. An implosion core with a plasma about a kilometer in diameter could power an artificial construct the size of a small moon. A couple of large ice asteroids for fuel&hellip;common enough still in the outer fringe systems&hellip;|Raith Sienar|<ref name="RP" />}}
The Expeditionary Battle Planetoid was the first true precursor to the designs that would eventually give birth to the Death Star project. The design was similar to the Death Star with a massive planet-devastating turbolaser powered by its core, but this design was deemed impractical due to the immense power generation needed to fuel such a weapon.<ref name="DSOTM">''[[Death Star Owner's Technical Manual]]''</ref> It would have been powered by an inner [[Plasma/Legends|plasma]] implosion core over a kilometer wide. [[Raith Sienar/Legends|Raith Sienar]] planned to [[Fuel/Legends|fuel]] it using large [[Water/Legends|ice]] [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroids]] that were common in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] [[Star system/Legends|systems]]. It also included two smaller spheres, attached to the poles of the main sphere (which was around 90-100 [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometers]] wide). Sienar considered removing these spheres to make the design more wieldy for transport.<ref name="RP" />

==History==
{{Quote|What a sense of scale! What unutterable ''power''!|[[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Wilhuff Tarkin]]|<ref name="RP" />}}
[[File:Raith_sienar-DSOTM.png|thumb|250px|Raith Sienar, the Wizard of Coruscant]]
Raith Sienar began designing the Expeditionary Battle Planetoid in [[29 BBY/Legends|29 BBY]]. While the project's construction would be highly expensive, Sienar was confident that it was completely doable. The battle station served as one of Sienar's show projects that he would show to potential clients and contractors with grandiose taste to impress them. He displayed its schematics to representatives of the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]], but they showed no interest in it due to their lack of imagination, according to Sienar.<ref name="RP" />

Around the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the [[Second Battle of Zonama Sekot|Second Battle of]] [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]], Raith Sienar presented the plans for the Battle Planetoid to [[Outland Regions Security Force/Legends|Republic Outland Regions Security Force]] [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Wilhuff Tarkin]], who was enamored of the idea.<ref name="RP" /> Tarkin turned around and showed the plans to then-[[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]], taking credit for them as well. Sienar, however, had since abandoned the idea of developing the weapon himself, and appeared indifferent to the apparent backstabbing.<ref name="DSn">[[Death Star (novel)|''Death Star'']]</ref>

In 29 BBY, the design was still considered impossible, as it required particular advances in [[Hypermatter/Legends|hypermatter]] technology in order to become fully feasible.<ref name="RP" /> The issues were solved by [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]] (and were the cause of [[Republic Sienar Systems/Legends|Republic Sienar Systems]]' grant to the [[Ministry of Science (Galactic Republic)/Legends|Ministry of Science]] for hypermatter research) thanks to the advances made by the [[Engineer/Legends|engineer]] [[Bevel Lemelisk]] .<ref name="HNN53150">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|50|business/1344_2.html|Ministry of Science Continues Hypermatter Studies}}</ref><ref name="DSOTM" />

With the formation of the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]] in the [[Standard month/Legends|months]] before the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|outbreak]] of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], Palpatine&mdash;as [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Sidious&mdash;gave the plans to his [[Sith apprentice/Legends|Sith apprentice]] and Confederate leader, [[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]]. The [[Geonosian/Legends|Geonosians]] took the designs and from them developed their [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Ultimate Weapon]], transforming the Battle Planetoid with a functional superlaser into a planet-killing [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon]].

After the [[Declaration of a New Order]] in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]], the Ultimate Weapon's design was refined into that of the Death Star, and construction on the station began and, ostensibly as a reward for "his" design, Tarkin became the [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] overseeing the project.

